1. Unsound financial information can lead to inaccurate budgeting and forecasting.
2. Decisions based on flawed data can result in misallocation of resources.
3. Poor quality information hinders the ability to track performance and outcomes effectively.
4. Relying on unsound information can undermine trust and confidence in agency leadership.
5. Inaccurate financial data can lead to non-compliance with legal and regulatory requirements.